Notebook[{

Cell[CellGroupData[{
Cell["Analytical Surface Master Integrals for Cube LS Stiffness", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"608b8499-f733-4b01-9661-37e3c4d4ecfd"],

Cell["\<\
The LS-convolved stiffness surface contribution involves 5D integrals (3D \
volume x 2D face) with a 1/|r-r'| Green's tensor singularity.  \
CubeT27Stiffness_LS.wl evaluated these numerically (~3500 s). 

This notebook develops the ANALYTICAL evaluation, showing that the surface \
master integrals reduce to the SAME family Mp[p,q,r] as the body bilinear \
(CubeGalerkin27.wl). The key is the (sigma, xi, v) substitution.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"26746d87-6779-43dc-9dae-79ed039b9f54"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["1. The Surface Integral", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"28537c11-a9c0-4314-8dda-c714e27ddb85"],

Cell["\<\
For a cube [-1,1]^3 with face F_n^+ at r_n = +1 (outward normal e_n):

  BstiffSurf[alpha,beta] = Sum over faces of
    Integral_cube phi_alpha_i(r) G_ij(r - r') t_j^(beta)(r') dS(r') dV(r)

where G_ij = a0/|x| delta_ij + b0 x_i x_j/|x|^3 (Kelvin form)
and t^(beta) = (Dc : epsilon(phi_beta)) . n is the traction on the face.

The A-channel (a0 part, isotropic) and B-channel (b0 part, anisotropic)
are computed separately.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"6349bef0-fe42-43b7-a921-a6f423f27818"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["2. Basis Modes and Their Tractions", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"0ae2acb7-8012-4e61-905e-8bb9e93ebe86"],

Cell["\<\
The T_27 basis has 3 constant displacements + 18 S-type quadratics (r_a^2 \
e_p) + 6 X-type quadratics (r_b r_c e_p, b != c).

For any polynomial mode phi, the traction on face F_n^s (coordinate n, sign s \
= +/-1) is a polynomial in the two face coordinates.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"f886e524-b6c7-4920-9292-cadda06da1a1"],

Cell["\<\
(* Strain tensor of a monomial mode phi = r1^n1 r2^n2 r3^n3 * e_p *)
strainOfMode[{n1_, n2_, n3_}, p_, {r1_, r2_, r3_}] := 
  Module[{phi, eps},
    phi = Table[KroneckerDelta[k, p] r1^n1 r2^n2 r3^n3, {k, 3}];
    eps = Table[
      (D[phi[[k]], {r1, r2, r3}[[l]]] + D[phi[[l]], {r1, r2, r3}[[k]]])/2,
      {k, 3}, {l, 3}];
    eps
  ]

(* Stress: sigma = Dlam tr(eps) I + 2 Dmu eps *)
stressOfMode[{n1_, n2_, n3_}, p_, {r1_, r2_, r3_}, Dlam_, Dmu_] :=
  Module[{eps, trEps},
    eps = strainOfMode[{n1, n2, n3}, p, {r1, r2, r3}];
    trEps = Sum[eps[[k, k]], {k, 3}];
    Table[Dlam trEps KroneckerDelta[k, l] + 2 Dmu eps[[k, l]], {k, 3}, {l, \
3}]
  ]

(* Traction on face with normal axis n, sign s *)
tractionOnFace[{n1_, n2_, n3_}, p_, faceAxis_, faceSign_, Dlam_, Dmu_] :=
  Module[{r1, r2, r3, sig, coords, trac},
    coords = {r1, r2, r3};
    sig = stressOfMode[{n1, n2, n3}, p, coords, Dlam, Dmu];
    trac = Table[sig[[k, faceAxis]], {k, 3}];
    (* Evaluate at the face: r_faceAxis = faceSign *)
    trac /. coords[[faceAxis]] -> faceSign
  ]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"7aca46ed-f4c0-410b-9d2a-d0096c7a5d12"],

Cell["\<\
(* Example: S-type mode r1^2 e1, traction on face z = +1 *)
tractionOnFace[{2, 0, 0}, 1, 3, 1, Dlam, Dmu] // Simplify\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"5e1f86de-f739-4aae-aa1c-e5ee599ea041"],

Cell["\<\
(* Example: S-type mode r3^2 e3, traction on face z = +1 *)
tractionOnFace[{0, 0, 2}, 3, 3, 1, Dlam, Dmu] // Simplify\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"e4e48b9c-5a27-4995-ac0e-be03ac4de085"],

Cell["\<\
(* Example: X-type mode r1 r2 e3, traction on face z = +1 *)
tractionOnFace[{1, 1, 0}, 3, 3, 1, Dlam, Dmu] // Simplify\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"2958272d-2bed-4d2c-8e45-4e9829378bd6"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["3. The Key Substitution: (\[Sigma], \[Xi], v)", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"04ee4353-74cb-4ab0-8862-8425202b27d0"],

Cell["\<\
For face F_3^+ (r'_3 = 1), the integration variables are:
  r = (r1, r2, r3) in [-1,1]^3  (volume point)
  s = (s1, s2)    in [-1,1]^2  (face point, r'=(s1,s2,1))

For the two SHARED coordinates (r_a, s_a) for a = 1,2:
  sigma_a = (r_a + s_a)/2,   xi_a = (r_a - s_a)/2
  r_a = sigma_a + xi_a,       s_a = sigma_a - xi_a
  Jacobian: |d(r,s)/d(sigma,xi)| = 2 per pair
  Domain: |sigma_a| + |xi_a| <= 1  (diamond)

For the NORMAL coordinate:
  v = (1 - r3)/2,  so r3 = 1 - 2v,  v in [0,1]
  dr3 = -2 dv

The displacement vector r - r' becomes:
  x1 = r1 - s1 = 2 xi1
  x2 = r2 - s2 = 2 xi2
  x3 = r3 - 1  = -2v

  |x| = 2 sqrt(xi1^2 + xi2^2 + v^2) = 2 rho

The singularity is at (xi1, xi2, v) = (0,0,0), i.e. when the volume
point touches the face at the same location as the surface point.

CRUCIAL: By octant symmetry of the diamond domain, we restrict to
sigma_a >= 0, xi_a >= 0 and multiply by 4 per pair (16 total).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4d7d0243-428e-43d6-9940-337bc5a95b61"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["4. Sigma Integrals Factor Out", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"36c7d14a-25c6-4155-92f7-f17c7ac902a4"],

Cell["\<\
After substitution, the integrand is:
  P(sigma1, xi1, sigma2, xi2, v) / rho

where P is a polynomial (from phi_alpha and traction).
Each sigma_a integral over [0, 1-xi_a] is elementary:

  Integral_0^{1-xi} sigma^k dsigma = (1-xi)^{k+1} / (k+1)

This removes sigma from the integrand, leaving a polynomial in 
(xi1, xi2, v) divided by rho = sqrt(xi1^2 + xi2^2 + v^2).

Expanding (1-xi)^n in powers of xi and collecting, we get a sum of
MASTER INTEGRALS:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"1670595f-f557-4820-80f3-bce3c841b7b3"],

Cell["\<\
(* ================================================================ *)
(* THE KEY RESULT: Surface master integrals ARE body master integrals *)
(* ================================================================ *)

(* Definition: *)
Mp[p_, q_, r_] /; !OrderedQ[{p, q, r}] := Mp @@ Sort[{p, q, r}]

(* Numerical evaluation *)
MpNum[p_, q_, r_] := NIntegrate[
  x^p y^q z^r / Sqrt[x^2 + y^2 + z^2],
  {x, 0, 1}, {y, 0, 1}, {z, 0, 1},
  PrecisionGoal -> 15, MaxRecursion -> 25
]

(* Symbolic evaluation *)
MpSym[p_, q_, r_] := Integrate[
  x^p y^q z^r / Sqrt[x^2 + y^2 + z^2],
  {x, 0, 1}, {y, 0, 1}, {z, 0, 1}
]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"bb5e8b44-acdc-4b80-8ee4-a167f0c7e9bf"],

Cell["\<\
The integral Js[p,q,r] = Integral_[0,1]^3 xi1^p xi2^q v^r / rho d(xi1) d(xi2) \
dv
is IDENTICAL to Mp[p,q,r] because:
  - The domain [0,1]^3 is the same
  - The denominator sqrt(xi1^2 + xi2^2 + v^2) is fully symmetric
  - The monomial xi1^p xi2^q v^r is just a relabeling

So Js[p,q,r] = Mp[p,q,r] by definition. No new integrals needed!

All existing Mp values from CubeGalerkin27.wl can be reused.
We just need additional values at higher exponents.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2851e1c1-8436-4abd-80bd-e18c1c46af0f"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["5. Needed Master Integrals", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6356ba33-02a5-4f1d-9d0e-5c5f37c77156"],

Cell["\<\
Maximum monomial degrees after the sigma integration:
  - xi1, xi2: up to degree 4 (from quadratic mode x sigma integral)
  - v: up to degree 2 (from r3 = 1 - 2v, quadratic modes)

By full permutation symmetry, we use canonical sorted form p >= q >= r.
With max index 4 in any position:\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"2b20be5c-397f-42a3-bdb6-d37cbf9ed616"],

Cell["\<\
(* Enumerate all needed sorted triples *)
neededMp = Union[Sort /@ Flatten[
  Table[{p, q, r}, {p, 0, 4}, {q, 0, 4}, {r, 0, 2}],
  2]];
Print[\"Number of unique master integrals: \", Length[neededMp]];
Print[\"Triples: \", neededMp];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"7546338c-152a-46bb-9f00-3cab097b8021"],

Cell["\<\
(* Compute all needed values numerically first (for validation) *)
Print[\"Computing numerical values...\"];
mpNumTable = Association[
  Table[
    Module[{sorted = Sort[triple]},
      sorted -> MpNum @@ sorted
    ],
    {triple, neededMp}
  ]
];
Print[\"Done. Sample values:\"];
Print[\"  Mp[0,0,0] = \", mpNumTable[{0,0,0}]];
Print[\"  Mp[1,0,0] = \", mpNumTable[{1,0,0}]];
Print[\"  Mp[1,1,0] = \", mpNumTable[{1,1,0}]];
Print[\"  Mp[1,1,1] = \", mpNumTable[{1,1,1}]];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"95f81ab0-26e4-42df-a6f6-f0fe4ad2ea50"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["6. Analytical Evaluation Strategy", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"06193ada-f6d5-48df-bd2a-3737a45dde90"],

Cell["\<\
Strategy: integrate v first, then xi2, then xi1.

Step 1 (v integral):
  Integral_0^1 v^r / sqrt(xi1^2 + xi2^2 + v^2) dv

This has closed forms for each r:
  r=0: ArcSinh[1/R] where R = sqrt(xi1^2 + xi2^2)
  r=1: sqrt(R^2 + 1) - R
  r=2: (1/2) sqrt(R^2+1) - (R^2/2) ArcSinh[1/R]

Step 2 (xi2 integral): polynomial in xi2 times these functions of R.
Step 3 (xi1 integral): similar reduction.

Each step involves integrals Mathematica can handle symbolically.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c8be47e8-ef49-4f14-bebc-4985e543f303"],

Cell["\<\
(* Step 1: v integral, parametric in R^2 = xi1^2 + xi2^2 *)
ClearAll[vIntegral];
vIntegral[r_, R_] := Integrate[v^r/Sqrt[R^2 + v^2], {v, 0, 1},
  Assumptions -> R > 0]

Print[\"v-integral closed forms:\"];
Do[
  Print[\"  r=\", r, \": \", Simplify[vIntegral[r, R]]],
  {r, 0, 2}
]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"32e01750-4ab0-477c-9afe-64d2a1446148"],

Cell["\<\
(* Attempt symbolic evaluation of specific Mp values *)
(* Start with the simplest: Mp[0,0,0] *)
Print[\"\\nAttempting symbolic Mp[0,0,0]...\"];
timing0 = AbsoluteTiming[
  mp000sym = Integrate[1/Sqrt[x^2 + y^2 + z^2],
    {z, 0, 1}, {y, 0, 1}, {x, 0, 1}]
];
Print[\"  Mp[0,0,0] = \", mp000sym, \"  (\", timing0[[1]], \" s)\"];
Print[\"  Numerical: \", N[mp000sym, 20]];
Print[\"  NIntegrate: \", mpNumTable[{0,0,0}]];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"5766aac0-9676-4228-a0f5-cd6742dde9f2"],

Cell["\<\
(* Mp[1,0,0]: one linear factor *)
Print[\"Attempting symbolic Mp[1,0,0]...\"];
timing1 = AbsoluteTiming[
  mp100sym = Integrate[x/Sqrt[x^2 + y^2 + z^2],
    {z, 0, 1}, {y, 0, 1}, {x, 0, 1}]
];
Print[\"  Mp[1,0,0] = \", mp100sym, \"  (\", timing1[[1]], \" s)\"];
Print[\"  N = \", N[mp100sym, 20]];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"364cf9cd-90ca-44e1-a3ea-15ef078bde8e"],

Cell["\<\
(* Automated: compute all needed Mp symbolically *)
(* WARNING: higher-order ones may take minutes. Start with small indices. *)
mpSymTable = <||>;
Do[
  Module[{triple = Sort[{p, q, r}], val, t},
    If[!KeyExistsQ[mpSymTable, triple],
      Print[\"Computing Mp\", triple, \"...\"];
      {t, val} = AbsoluteTiming[
        Integrate[
          x^triple[[1]] y^triple[[2]] z^triple[[3]] / Sqrt[x^2+y^2+z^2],
          {z, 0, 1}, {y, 0, 1}, {x, 0, 1}
        ]
      ];
      mpSymTable[triple] = val;
      Print[\"  = \", val, \"  (\", t, \" s)\"];
      Print[\"  N = \", N[val, 20], \"  (num: \", mpNumTable[triple], \")\"];
    ]
  ],
  (* Start with small indices first *)
  {r, 0, 2}, {q, r, 4}, {p, q, 4}
];\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"107a528b-8a09-47d9-9b39-92ffbe9cf904"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["7. B-Channel: Reduction via Integration by Parts", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"762c61e4-17ba-4b7c-b7ae-12f139142ba0"],

Cell["\<\
The B-channel has kernel x_i x_j / |x|^3 = 4 xi_a xi_b / (8 rho^3)
where (a,b) index the displacement components.

Key identity: xi_a / rho^3 = -(d/d(xi_a))(1/rho)

So integrals of the form
  Integral f(xi) * xi_a / rho^3 d(xi_a)
reduce via integration by parts to:
  [boundary terms at xi_a = 0, 1] + Integral f'(xi) / rho d(xi_a)

The boundary term at xi_a = 0 involves 1/sqrt(xi_b^2 + v^2) and
the term at xi_a = 1 involves 1/sqrt(1 + xi_b^2 + v^2).
Both are lower-dimensional integrals of the same type.

For the diagonal case xi_a^2 / rho^3, use:
  xi_a^2 / rho^3 = xi_a * (xi_a/rho^3) = -xi_a d(1/rho)/d(xi_a)
  = -d(xi_a/rho)/d(xi_a) + 1/rho
  = 1/rho - d(xi_a/rho)/d(xi_a)

So Integral f * xi_a^2/rho^3 = Integral f/rho - [boundary of f*xi_a/rho].\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"20702957-777e-46b8-966f-80da5705ab5a"],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
(* B-channel master integrals: xi_a xi_b / rho^3 type *)
(* These can be defined directly and compared *)
BpNum[i_, j_, p_, q_, r_] := NIntegrate[
  x^p y^q z^r * {x, y, z}[[i]] {x, y, z}[[j]] / (x^2 + y^2 + z^2)^(3/2),
  {x, 0, 1}, {y, 0, 1}, {z, 0, 1},
  PrecisionGoal -> 12, MaxRecursion -> 25
]

(* Verify IBP identity: Integral xi1^2/rho^3 = Integral 1/rho - boundary *)
Print[\"Verifying IBP identity...\"];
direct = BpNum[1, 1, 0, 0, 0];
fromMp = mpNumTable[{0, 0, 0}];
boundary = NIntegrate[
  1/Sqrt[1 + y^2 + z^2],
  {y, 0, 1}, {z, 0, 1},
  PrecisionGoal -> 15
];
Print[\"  Direct:   \", direct];
Print[\"  Mp[0,0,0] - boundary: \", fromMp - boundary];
Print[\"  Difference: \", direct - (fromMp - boundary)];\
\>", "Input",
 CellLabel->"In[7]:=",ExpressionUUID->"891e4e8a-ce1e-4294-92f2-127d40b74937"],

Cell[BoxData["\<\"Verifying IBP identity...\"\>"], "Print",
 CellChangeTimes->{3.984878692046619*^9},
 CellLabel->
  "During evaluation of \
In[7]:=",ExpressionUUID->"fba692ce-261b-4918-99b9-46f2a9298be1"],

